#. <section class="sutta" id="an5.106"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "an5.106:0.1"
msgid "Aṅguttara Nikāya 5"
msgstr "Numbered Discourses 5"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "an5.106:0.2"
msgid "11. Phāsuvihāravagga"
msgstr "11. Living Comfortably"

#. </p><h1>
msgctxt "an5.106:0.3"
msgid "106. Ānandasutta"
msgstr "106. With Ānanda"

#. </h1></div><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc1"></a>
msgctxt "an5.106:1.1"
msgid "Ekaṃ samayaṃ bhagavā kosambiyaṃ viharati ghositārāme."
msgstr ""
"At one time the Buddha was staying near Kosambi, in Ghosita’s Monastery."

msgctxt "an5.106:1.2"
msgid ""
"Atha kho āyasmā ānando yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā bhagavantaṃ "
"abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdi. Ekamantaṃ nisinno kho āyasmā ānando "
"bhagavantaṃ etadavoca:"
msgstr ""
"Then Venerable Ānanda went up to the Buddha, bowed, sat down to one side, "
"and said to him:"

# BB and Com don’t remark on “sangha” here, but presumably it means, “while living in a community”, as opposed to living in seclusion. It doesn’t mean “while remaining as a mendicant”.
#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pi" id="pts-vp-pli3.133"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc2"></a>
#. VAR: bhikkhu saṃghe → bhikkhusaṅgho (s1-3, pts1)
msgctxt "an5.106:2.1"
msgid ""
"“Kittāvatā nu kho, bhante, bhikkhu saṃghe viharanto phāsuṃ vihareyyā”ti?"
msgstr ""
"“Sir, how could a mendicant live comfortably while staying in a Saṅgha "
"community?”"

# Sampavatta is unusual, “motivate” is more literal than BB’s “exhort”, which follows the Comm.
#. VAR: attanā → attanā ca (pts1, mr)
#. VAR: no → no ca (mr)
#. VAR: sampavattā → sampavattā hoti (mr)
msgctxt "an5.106:2.2"
msgid ""
"“Yato kho, ānanda, bhikkhu attanā sīlasampanno hoti, no paraṃ adhisīle "
"sampavattā;"
msgstr ""
"“It’s when a mendicant is accomplished in their own ethical conduct, but "
"they don’t motivate others to be ethical."

msgctxt "an5.106:2.3"
msgid "ettāvatāpi kho, ānanda, bhikkhu saṃghe viharanto phāsuṃ vihareyyā”ti."
msgstr ""
"That’s how a mendicant could live comfortably while staying in a Saṅgha "
"community.”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc3"></a>
msgctxt "an5.106:3.1"
msgid ""
"“Siyā pana, bhante, aññopi pariyāyo yathā bhikkhu saṃghe viharanto phāsuṃ "
"vihareyyā”ti?"
msgstr ""
"“But sir, could there be another way for a mendicant to live comfortably "
"while staying in an Order?”"

#. VAR: ānanda → ānandāti bhagavā avoca (s1-3, pts1)
msgctxt "an5.106:3.2"
msgid "“Siyā, ānanda."
msgstr "“There could, Ānanda."

msgctxt "an5.106:3.3"
msgid ""
"Yato kho, ānanda, bhikkhu attanā sīlasampanno hoti, no paraṃ adhisīle "
"sampavattā;"
msgstr ""
